\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups unbleached flour, plus more for rolling berries\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon baking powder\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/3 cup sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup unsalted butter, chilled and cut in chunks\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup buttermilk or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cream}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 egg\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pint fresh blueberries\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.\
In a large bowl, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sift/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sift}} together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; mix thoroughly. Cut in butter using 2 forks or a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pastry-blender/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pastry blender}}. The butter pieces should be coated with flour and resemble crumbs.\
In another bowl, mix buttermilk and egg together, and then add to the flour mixture. Mix just to incorporate, do no overwork the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dough/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 dough}}.\
Roll blueberries in flour to coat, this will help prevent the fruit from sinking to the bottom of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/scone/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 scone}} when baked. Fold the blueberries into {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/batter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 batter}}, being careful not to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/bruise/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 bruise}}. Drop large tablespoons of batter on an ungreased {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookie/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cookie}} sheet.\
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until brown. Cool before applying orange glaze.\
